The paper discusses the design and experimentation of shaping techniques for next-generation optical communications, which involves information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), optical communications (cs.OH), data centers (cs.DC), and probability and statistics (cs.PF). The paper specifically focuses on the comparison of circular 64-QAM and square 64-QAM, which are modulation schemes used in optical communications.
